reviews.review_text: IT MUST HAVE BEEN 100 DEGREES INSIDE THIS SHOW WAS OF THE BEATEN PATH,BUT TYPICAL FOR A COLLEGE SHOW FROM '79. THE MUSIC WAS WELL PLAYED FOR SURE BUT NOTHING REALLY MIND BENDING OTHER THAN THE FACT GARCIA WORE I AM PRETTY SURE RED SHIRT AND WHITE PANTS.TO GET IN TO THE GYM WHERE THEY WERE PLAYING SECURITY JUST OPENED UP 5 OR SO GARAGE DOORS AND EVERYONE STREAMED IN UNTOUCHED.THE PLACE WAS UNGODLY HOT.TWO SETS AND AN ENCORE AND WE WERE OFF TO PENN STATE NOW THAT SHOW GOT PRETTY HEAVY UP IN HAPPY VALLEY AND JUDGING FROM THE MUSIC JERRY AND COMPANY DUG BEING IN HAPPY VALLEY AND SO DID WE.
